<div class="two-fifths">
  <p>
    Shelby.tv uses a total of two font families. Helvetica is the work horse, it's used for everything from in-app UI to long form copy in various marketing situations. Ubuntu is more decorative and works well at large sizes, it's main utility is for headlines on landing page and marketing materials.
  </p>

  <small class="annotation">
    <p>
      In order to keep the page load reasonable, Ubuntu is limited to two weights: 300, and 400. Helvetica is a universal typeface (that can fall back to Arial, for Windows) and doesn't need to be stored on our servers.
    </p>
  </small>
